[Outbreaks of mumps still occur sporadically throughout Europe as a
result of incomplete vaccine coverage in the past, particularly in
countries with significant migrant Roma populations that may escape
routine immunisation programs. The inclusion of a sub-optimal mump
component in triple MMR vaccine in the past may be another factor
affecting the efficacy of vaccination. (E.g. Higher rates of aseptic
meningitis have been attributed to the Urabe, Leningrad-Zagreb and
Leningrad-3 strain vaccines compared with the current Jeryl-Lynn strain vaccine
<http://www.who.int/vaccine_safety/topics/mumps/statement/en/>.)
A map of Bulgaria can be viewed at:
<http://education.yahoo.com/reference/factbook/bu/map.html;_ylt=AtDijegFEGPd.km6_uIUY864ecYF>.
- Mod.CP]
